comments.body:
This may be related to one of our plugins, the [princeton shim](https://github.com/hudmol/as_princeton_shim). It was developed for v3.2 but we're on v3.3. 

These are the three things it does:

1. ANW-1495: Support for Local Access Restriction Type in spreadsheet importer
2. ANW-1489: URIs in EAD exports
3. NO JIRA: Support for Local Access Restriction Type and structured restriction dates in RDE

The shim was developed for core. If the functionality is going to be part of 3.4, then we can (and should) turn the plugin off when we upgrade.

Could we rename group vars files for auto-loading?

comments.body:
Managing "one-off" SSH keys for individual groups or machines is a challenge when we run a single playbook against an entire environment at once, given our current `group_vars` setup.

I've done a small proof-of-concept here for the simplest idea in #3925 - adding a file called `/group_vars/figgy_production.yml` meant those variables automatically loaded into the playbook for machines in the `figgy_production` inventory group. We definitely need a broader discussion about this, though.
